Konoha, who felt unwell and sensed discomfort in
her body, slowly opened her eyes... In front of
her stood a man, looking down at her with eyes
that seemed to see her as trash.

Poor little kitten, isn't it... You must be
Konoha, a magical girl, right?

I am the owner of this gambling den, Jackal. It
seems you caused quite a ruckus, huh?

Well, of course! It was a complete mess, that kind
of thing.

It seems you don't understand gambling, huh? In
the world of gambling, you have to do whatever it
takes to win. But let's put that aside for now and
explain the Slave Mark.

I am the owner of this gambling den, Jackal. It's
quite unusual for someone like you to willingly
accept the Slave Mark. You're different, aren't
you?
Yes, I... hear that a lot...

Well... there certainly are girls who come here
willingly. Maybe they don't really understand what
the Slave Mark is, so I'll explain it just in
case...

The Slave Mark grants absolute obedience to the
master. It's impossible for a slave to escape from
this slum city on their own.
I didn't hear anything like that... Ugh...

And until you repay your debt, it's impossible for
a slave to lay a hand on their master. This mark
won't be lifted.

All money management is entrusted to a man named
Moran from Moomoo Finance... So, it's best to ask
him about repayment.

You're free to earn money however you want within
the underground slum city. But when you come back
here, you'll have to entertain a certain man.

I... If I were to get pregnant... What would
happen... I can't possibly give birth...

What are you talking about? Everyone is the same.
Not everyone can give birth, but they work hard.
Well, at least in the beginning.

If you can't repay the specified amount every day,
the penalty is that the number of days of
confinement will increase each time.

If the number of confinement days increases, the
possibility of getting pregnant and giving birth
also becomes higher, you know.

(This... might have been too easy... I may have
underestimated the power of the slave mark...)
